        <div class="step">
          <div class="num">2</div>
          <div>
            <h3>Buy & Configure a Number</h3>
            <p>Purchase a virtual number (local, mobile, or toll-free). Enable SMS, voice, or both. Configure caller ID and messaging preferences.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <div class="num">3</div>
          <div>
            <h3>Set Up SMS & Messaging Webhooks</h3>
            <p>Point incoming SMS/MMS and web messages to your backend. Example using Express.js:</p>
            <pre>app.post('/sms', (req,res) => {
  const msg = req.body.Body;
  const from = req.body.From;
  // handle message
  res.send('&lt;Response&gt;&lt;Message&gt;Thanks!&lt;/Message&gt;&lt;/Response&gt;');
});</pre>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <div class="num">4</div>
          <div>
            <h3>Enable Business Calling</h3>
            <p>Use SIP or VoIP APIs to make/receive calls from your web app. Forward calls to support agents or mobile devices as needed.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <div class="num">5</div>
          <div>
            <h3>Add Number Masking</h3>
            <p>Protect privacy by using proxy numbers for calls/messages. Common in marketplaces and delivery apps.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <div class="num">6</div>
          <div>
